    Dealing with stereotype threat is always difficult to do especially since we believe that social reforms have changed (id urge you to click on the title of this blog) and that raising an issue of sexism is, in and of itself taboo. Although I did not raise any attention to my most recent experience at work (or any previous ones), I plan to act on and stop any form of sexist remarks- intentional or not. I plan on providing meaningful feedback by asking that individual if they would have talked that way to another male. If not why? If so, touché. I can already tell that I will be surrounded by considerate individuals at DBC, so if I were to mention that I felt as if I was being talked down to or stereotyped for being a female, I think the feedback would be welcomed. At least I hope so. I have also been made out to feel like I was making a fuss out of what seemed to be nothing in the past.
  </p>
